    "size_difference_main_reason": "The CMIP6 reference and SWOOSH files both store vmro3 as float32, so the 41 MB vs 17 MB difference is not caused by double vs float32 precision in vmro3. The common variables also use the same zlib level, shuffle setting, fletcher32 setting, and chunking as the reference. The remaining size difference is therefore due to HDF5/NetCDF4 compressibility of the actual data values: the SWOOSH ozone field compresses substantially better than the CMIP6 reference field."
